C

checkInvariants - Static variable in class Tray
If you want Tray to perform an invariants check after each call to the constructor or the moveBlock method (which are the only "setter" methods in Tray), set this variable to true.
clone() - Method in class Tray
Returns a deep copy of this Tray.
colIdx - Variable in class Point
Represents the column index of this Point within a Tray.
collidesWith(Block) - Method in class Block
Checks whether there are any common Points shared by this Block and the given Block.
colSize - Variable in class Tray
Represents the number of columns in this tray.
computePerfectHash(short, short, short, short) - Static method in class Block
Returns a perfect hash value for the hypothetical Block corresponding to the given arguments.
configurationsSeen - Static variable in class Solver
This set keeps track of all the configurations that the solver has encountered, so that memoization prevents infinite loops from occurring during solution search.
containsBlock(Block) - Method in class Tray
Checks whether the given Block is in this Tray.
containsPoint(Point) - Method in class Block
Checks whether the given Point is contained within the range occupied by this Block.
createBlock(String) - Static method in class Solver
Scans through the given String, which must be in the format "ULrow ULcol LRrow LRcol", and returns the corresponding Block.
